       Youth Programs

      Job Corps Youth Opportunities state and local grants youth corner
      apprenticeship training [library.jpg]

   Welcome !

   Youth programs are administered by the Office of Youth Services (OYS),
   Employment and Training Administration (ETA), U.S. Department of Labor
   and funded in State and local communities. Our web site provides
   information and assistance about various youth employment and training
   activities authorized under the Workforce Investment Act (WIA) of 1998,
   29 USC ยง 2801 et.seq. (P.L. 105-220) on August 7, 1998.

